** The role: **   
** **   
The Engineering Superintendent is responsible for overseeing and managing the
Engineering department. The position is responsible for developing,
supervising, monitoring and reviewing engineering standards to ensure
compliance with industry regulations and best practices. The position will
manage the engineering team providing guidance and support to engineers and
technicians.  
The position will allocate resources, set goals, and ensure the timely
completion of engineering project deliverables. This role involves a high
level or coordination and communications with other departments.  
Additionally, the position shall be involved in the recruitment, training, and
performance evaluation of engineering staff.  
  
The Engineering Superintendent will be responsible for all design verification
as well as ownership of site standards, drawings, and specifications.  
  
** Role Accountabilities: **   

  * Execute engineering design projects, both internal and external, overseeing drawing approvals and resource allocation. 
  * Lead the technical review of engineering design drawing approvals by collaborating with cross-functional teams. 
  * Project manage engineering initiatives, ensuring deadlines and budgets are met, and provide regular progress reports. 
  * Facilitate value engineering and value management activities. 
  * Manage job numbers and staff resources for client engineering projects. 
  * Drive research and development projects and establish a consistent project management framework. 
  

  * Cultivate relationships with subcontractors and vendors, ensuring quality laborand parts for projects. 
  * Innovate processes and reduce costs through continuous improvement initiatives. 
  * Collaborate across departments to identify and maximize cross-capability opportunities. 
  * Ensure work is conducted safely and efficiently, adhering to the company's WHS procedures. 
  * Stakeholder requirement specification (SRS) 
  * Further development of work scope 
  * Options scoping 
  * Key equipment selection. 
  * Resourcing and procurement of specific skills setting (special contractors or expertise required) 
  * Ensure all discipline Project Status Report inputs are entered in a timely manner for BI Reporting 
  * Sign off at design completion for design handover. 
  * Review and sign off scoping. 
  * Technical feasibility studies 
  * Engineering, detailed design, specification writing, and drafting of drawings at different gates for in-house works. 
  * Key equipment technical specifications. 
  
** Role description: **   

  * Participate in Project Morning Run meetings, 3 per week, and ensure all discipline inputs are included where required. 
  * Participate in P&E Interface and P&E Construction meetings, held weekly, and ensure all discipline requirements are understood by all participants. 
  * Run deliverability/ constructability assessment and technical feasibility. 
  * Run Safety in Design workshops and implement actions. 
  * Consider inputs and feedback from Construction Supplier 
  * Consider input and feedback from Operations team. 
  * Run constructability review meetings (HAZARD Study #2, #3) 
  * Engineering statutory compliance auditing and solution 
  * Review of designs provided by the Engineering Suppliers 
  * Engineering suppliers technical due diligence 
  * Design gates approvals. 
  * Quality management 
  * Design changes management. 
  *   * Attendance to Contractor’s Safety in Design workshops 
  * Establish uniform engineering and technical criteria, methods, processes and practices. 
  * Issue Construction Handover package to Construction Supplier 
** Qualifications: **   
Tertiary qualification in an Engineering, Project Management or related
discipline, or equivalent experience in the workplace.  
** Behavioural competencies: **   
· Demonstrates personal responsibility for own health and safety whilst
setting clear expectations of relevant legal obligations, safe workplace
practices and HSE operating practices for others, holding them accountable for
their actions.  
· Assimilates and applies new job-related knowledge and skills received
through feedback, exposure, coaching and formal training.  
· Embodies and exemplifies Newmont’s vision and values.  
· Stays focused and composed in stressful situations.  
· Demonstrates the ability to work constructively with diverse groups and
cultures.  
** **   
